translated: Bolmsö, Jönköping. 1st child of P.N. Andersson and Alma Johansson. Married in 1939 to Ellen Johansson. — Attended high school in Lund in 1923, obtained a Bachelor of Arts degree there in 1928, a theology degree and practical theology certificate, and became ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1932. Served as an assistant pastor in Kärda and Båraryd, a curate in Våthult and Bosebo, and as a vicar at Tofteryd since 1942. In Våthult, among other things, served as chairman of the church council, the school board and the child protection committee, as a delegate to the diocesan council, and as the representative of Tofteryd's cemetery committee.
